data.title: Southeast Wisconsin weather: Winter Weather Advisory in effect until 9 a.m.
data.meta_description: Locations north of Milwaukee will see a mix of snow, sleet, and freezing rain through the night with 2-5" of snow possible.
data.text:
A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY is in effect for the following counties from 9 p.m. Wednesday to 9 a.m. Thursday: Fond du Lac, Jefferson, Ozaukee, Sheboygan, and Washington.

2-4" of heavy wet snow is expected with locally higher amounts near 6."

Travel will be dangerous Wednesday night and Thursday morning and should be avoided if possible.

_____________

Our next winter storm is approaching, and just like most prior systems this season, we're going to see primarily rain here in Milwaukee. We've seen a few lake effect snow showers already this afternoon, but look for the precipitation associated with the storm system to arrive after 8 p.m. this evening. Locations north of Milwaukee will see a mix of snow, sleet, and freezing rain through the night with 2-5" of snow possible. Mainly rain, with snow mixing in at times, is likely in Milwaukee and locations south, with around an inch of slush possible. Scattered rain and snow showers continue Thursday with little additional accumulation expected.

Relatively cooler conditions arrive for the rest of the week and into the weekend, but far from a January deep freeze.
